<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,351,629]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,532,557]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[799,1018,532,557]" class="Oligochaeta" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Metaphire" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="peguana">
<emphasis box="[799,1018,532,557]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Metaphire peguana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but was restored to full species rank by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[186,394,567,592]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2016) Darwin's earthworms (Annelida, Oligochaeta, Megadrilacea, Acanthodrilidae, Octochaetidae, Megascolecidae, Glossoscolecidae, Lumbricidae) with review of cosmopolitan Metaphire peguana - species group from Philippines. Opuscula Zoologic a, 47 (1), 09 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.18348 / opzool. 2016.1.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Blakemore (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[405,539,569,592]" class="Oligochaeta" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Metaphire" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="peguana">
<emphasis box="[405,539,569,592]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. peguana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[593,762,569,592]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pheretima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="saigonensis">
<emphasis box="[593,762,569,592]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. saigonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly different in the distance between male pores and spermathecal pores (
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[381,573,604,629]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2016) Darwin's earthworms (Annelida, Oligochaeta, Megadrilacea, Acanthodrilidae, Octochaetidae, Megascolecidae, Glossoscolecidae, Lumbricidae) with review of cosmopolitan Metaphire peguana - species group from Philippines. Opuscula Zoologic a, 47 (1), 09 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.18348 / opzool. 2016.1.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Blakemore 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
